{"word":"G1801 - ἐνωτίζομαι - enōtízomai - en-o-tid'-zom-ahee - Hearken","slug":"G1801","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐνωτίζομαι</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>enōtízomai"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>en-o-tid'-zom-ahee"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Hearken"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x0313;&#x03BD;&#x03C9;&#x03C4;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B6;&#x03BF;&#x03BC;&#x03B1;&#x03B9; - eno&#x0304;tizomai</b> - <i>en-o-tid'-zom-ahee</i><p/>Middle voice from a compound of <a href=\"#/G1722\">G1722</a> and <a href=\"#/G3775\">G3775</a>; to take <i>in one's ear</i>, that is, to <i>listen:</i> - hearken."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3775\">G3775</a>, <a href=\"#/G5621\">G5621</a>"}]}